projects: [{'title': 'Rapidly Deployable Rescue Vehicle', 'date': {'start': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, 'description': 'The Rapidly Deployable Rescue Vehicle (RDRV) is a remotely operated emergency floatation device with autonomous capabilities. The design of the RDRV allows it to assist emergency personnel by providing the initial floatation to victims during a marine rescue. The vehicle can be controlled manually, through radio frequency control, or autonomously via a digital compass, GPS module, and onboard Arduino Due microcontroller. The RDRV is capable of obtaining speeds greater than five miles per hour, providing a minimum of 15.5 pounds of buoyancy, facilitating audio communication between the operator and victim, and recording each mission using an onboard video recording device. Mission success required the vehicle to be remotely piloted to a victim located 328 feet offshore and to autonomously travel between programmable waypoints separated by 197 feet. The RDRV is two person deployable and was constructed within a budget $1,500.00 US dollars.
